---

KumoStack includes significant additions and modifications beyond the original
MiniStack codebase, including but not limited to:

- Real EKS clusters via k3s Docker containers with full kubectl access
- Real RDS databases via Docker containers (PostgreSQL, MySQL, MariaDB)
- Real Secrets Manager with persistent in-memory storage
- Service Control Policies (SCPs) with real enforcement at the API level
- AWS Organizations with management account gating
- Cross-account AssumeRole audit log
- CloudWatch with SEARCH expression support for Grafana integration
- Live Infrastructure Architecture diagram (ReactFlow)
- Stackport Resource Browser with full CRUD
- Grafana integration with CloudWatch, Prometheus, and Loki dashboards
- Vector.dev 3-tier log pipeline (Loki + S3 + Garage)
- Garage self-hosted S3 for Terraform state and log cold archives

---

Third-party and open-source components used by KumoStack:

- LocalStack — inspired patterns for AWS service emulation
  https://github.com/localstack/localstack (Apache 2.0)

- k3s by Rancher Labs — lightweight Kubernetes for EKS emulation
  https://github.com/k3s-io/k3s (Apache 2.0)

- Grafana — observability dashboards
  https://github.com/grafana/grafana (AGPLv3)

- Loki — log aggregation system by Grafana Labs
  https://github.com/grafana/loki (AGPLv3)

- Vector — high-performance observability data pipeline
  https://github.com/vectordotdev/vector (MPL 2.0)

- Garage — S3-compatible distributed object storage
  https://git.deuxfleurs.fr/Deuxfleurs/garage (AGPLv3)

- Prometheus — monitoring and alerting toolkit
  https://github.com/prometheus/prometheus (Apache 2.0)

- ReactFlow — interactive node-based UI library
  https://github.com/xyflow/xyflow (MIT)

